      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KYVALLEY JUDGE (3) added to a string of wins and placings when he covered ground but got home by 1.4 metres at Bendigo last time. Progressive trotter who is three from three at this distance range and should have no excuses from this advantageous draw. RUN FOREST RUN NZ (10) switches back to a mobile start and and broke the last time he attempted one but has gone well since, winning two back at Birchip and placing last week at Bendigo. Good enough if he gets it right. FAITH FULL (2) has had tougher barriers and been let down by manners when tackling stronger company of late. Has the benefit of a good draw and has won both previous attempts here so could find her best. TICTOK (6) has been ticking along well and should be competitive. MY JERRY (5) hasn't raced for two years but is capable and has been trialling well so watch the betting.",
